“You are a senior React developer who specializes in performance optimization and accessibility
. Create a responsive business dashboard page using a modern UI framework (such as Material-UI or Ant Design) that meets these requirements:

Data Table with Virtualization: Render large datasets (10,000+ rows) efficiently using row virtualization
.
Lightweight Bundle: Ensure the bundle size remains small (e.g. under 50KB gzipped) by using code-splitting and tree shaking
.
Accessibility (ARIA Compliance): All interactive elements (tables, buttons, navigation) must be fully keyboard-navigable and ARIA-labeled
.
Error Handling: Implement robust error handling everywhere
: network failures, invalid user input, and empty states should display friendly messages. Do not leave any unhandled exception.
Testing: Provide comprehensive tests (Jest or similar) with ≥80% coverage
 for all components and utility functions. Include edge cases.
Documentation: Include clear comments/JSDoc for each component and function
.
Performance: Optimize render cycles (e.g. use React.memo, avoid unnecessary re-renders) and implement lazy loading for heavy components
.
Responsive & Business-Centric UI: Use a clean, uncluttered design (ample whitespace, limited color palette) and a layout that prioritizes key metrics at the top
. Ensure mobile-first responsiveness – e.g. simplify layout on small screens, enable collapsible side navigation
.
Authentication & Security: If applicable, handle login/logout flows securely, and never expose sensitive data in error messages.
Iterative Explanation: Provide a brief step-by-step reasoning of your approach before giving the final implementation
.”
